In the Stone Age amber ornaments were the favorite articles of personal adornment‚ as the graves of the period testify. In the Bronze Age amber ceased to be so highly favored among the northern peoples‚ who had learned to know bronze and gold, but it became an article of commerce and was spread by various trade routes over Mediterranean and Western Europe, where it was eagerly wel- comed.
